Hi Océane,
I expect the error comes from here:

github.com

cms-analysis/HiggsAnalysis-CombinedLimit/blob/102x/src/CMSHistFunc.cc#L166

for (unsigned i = 0; i < hpoints_[0].size(); ++i) {
dm[i] = hpoints_[0][i] - hpoints_[0][0];
M(i, 0) = 1.;
if (i > 0) M(0, i) = 0.;
}
for (unsigned i = 1; i < hpoints_[0].size(); ++i) {
for (unsigned j = 1; j < hpoints_[0].size(); ++j) {
M(i, j) = std::pow(dm[i], (double)j);
}
}
global_.m = M.Invert();

global_.c_scale.resize(hpoints_[0].size(), 0.);
global_.c_sum.resize(hpoints_[0].size(), 0.);
// End
global_.means.resize(hpoints_[0].size(), 0.);
global_.sigmas.resize(hpoints_[0].size(), 0.);
global_.slopes.resize(hpoints_[0].size(), 0.);
global_.offsets.resize(hpoints_[0].size(), 0.);
}
}

In fact this is the code that’s preparing some of the internal information for the moment morphing. So it doesn’t affect the integral morphing method you are using now. But maybe it will be a problem if you switch to the moment morphing. It’s not immediately clear to me why this error should be triggered, but it may not matter, depending the “MomentSetting” used (can try linear first).
cheers,
Andrew
